<emphasis id="B3E260B6AED5A9C3AB522F7285ED758A" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">Pilea nidiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis id="6EFD16C5FD2B52602C40277DF4D4BB38" bold="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">A</emphasis>
Habit; note the unequal leaf laminae at each node 
<emphasis id="A1A79DEA4AABD0B946C394BA53436456" bold="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">B</emphasis>
Leaf detail (major lamina upper surface) showing cystoliths 
<emphasis id="3156756ADB9A8D0638F91E85104A77B4" bold="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">C</emphasis>
Stipules and stem covered with cystoliths 
<emphasis id="DAD4C42D33F28F43D9383CDD7FDDE519" bold="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">D</emphasis>
Staminate inflorescence 
<emphasis id="472CE4732A868760129A9E61EC62A9CC" bold="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">E</emphasis>
Infructescence 
<emphasis id="154E73A7929491F1256E360402EF4E1F" bold="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">F, G</emphasis>
Pistillate flowers with developing achenes. (
<emphasis id="B5C0CE8B2B73A6F8056FF56A7B3B153B" bold="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">A, D</emphasis>
from 
